==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semidome
<hw>Sem"i*dome`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>A roof or ceiling covering a semicircular room or recess, or one of
nearly that shape, as the apse of a church, a niche, or the like. It is
approximately the quarter of a hollow sphere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semidouble</ent>⟦br⟧
